    <h2 style="text-decoration: underline; text-align: center">
        What does a Benefit Consultant do?</h2>
    <br/>
        <h3 style="text-align: center">The consultant explores a person&#39;s employment plan and/or Social Security 
            Benefits assisting the individual in the ability to become employed and/or 
            secure their Social Security Benefits </h3>
    <h3 style="text-align: center">when working.</h3><br />
    <h3 style="text-align: center">This results in the person gaining greater economic self-sufficiency.</h3><br />
    <h2 style="text-align: left">The consultant:</h2>
    
    <ul>
        <li>
            <h3>
                Calculates the individual's wages and explains how the income affects the person's Social Security benefits.</h3>
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Provides the individual with information about government resources for employment.</h3>
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Quarterly reviews the person's record keeping and work related benefits.</h3>
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Provides and explains tools necessary to maintain adequate record keeping for Social Security reporting.</h3>
        </li>
        <br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Offers One-on-One consulting when requested and by appointment.</h3>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <br />
